Let me work through each ratio step by step:

1. Return on Equity (ROE) = Net Profit / Total Owner's Equity
   - Net Profit: $146,127.58 (from income statement)
   - Total Owner's Equity: $16,146,127.58 (from balance sheet, end amount)
   - ROE = $146,127.58 / $16,146,127.58 = 0.00905 = 0.905%

2. Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets

   - Total Assets: $21,662,106.19 (from balance sheet, end amount)
   - Debt to Asset Ratio = $5,515,978.61 / $21,662,106.19 = 0.2546 â‰ˆ 0.25

3. Gross Profit Margin = Gross Profit / Total Revenue
   - Gross Profit: $300,421.65 (from income statement)
   - Total Revenue: $863,371.65 (from income statement)
   - Gross Profit Margin = $300,421.65 / $863,371.65 = 0.3479 = 34.79%
